Ukraine’s Spring Grain Planting Advances 12%, Ministry Says

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-04-08T12:32:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/ukraine-s-spring-grain-planting-advances-12-ministry-says-1-.html
Ukraine’s spring grain planting
covered 2.2 million hectares (5.4 million acres) as of today, up
12 percent from a year earlier, the Agriculture Ministry said.  Spring barley covered 1.66 million hectares, the
Kiev-based ministry said in e-mailed statement today. Spring
wheat was planted on 195,000 hectares, sugar beets on 174,000
hectares and sunflower on 53,000 hectares, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  